1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,628
♪ <i>Oh, tailor…</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,712 --> 00:00:07,924
["Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,550 --> 00:00:10,427
- ♪ <i>Fix this</i> ♪
- ♪ <i>Oh, tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,510 --> 00:00:12,971
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:13,054 --> 00:00:15,265
♪ <i>One cut, and it's done</i> ♪

6
00:00:15,348 --> 00:00:16,641
♪ <i>In the chaos of the world</i> ♪

7
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:18,893
- [Chipper] <i>Where's Draco?</i>
- [guard] <i>The magician, boss.</i>

8
00:00:18,977 --> 00:00:20,770
[guard] <i>He's probably the one</i>
<i>who took the chicken.</i>

9
00:00:20,854 --> 00:00:22,313
[Chipper] <i>Useless!</i>

10
00:00:22,397 --> 00:00:23,940
[Chipper] <i>I'll kill that scumbag magician.</i>

11
00:00:24,023 --> 00:00:25,650
[man] Hey!

12
00:00:26,276 --> 00:00:28,111
- [Atoy] <i>We're heading out.</i>
- [Karla] <i>Oh, okay, okay.</i>

13
00:00:28,778 --> 00:00:30,196
- [gasping]
- [Tonet shrieks]

14
00:00:30,280 --> 00:00:31,656
- [Atoy] <i>Move, move, move!</i>
- [grunting]

15
00:00:31,740 --> 00:00:32,949
[Atoy] Let's go, let's go.

16
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:34,576
[guard] <i>Boss, they escaped!</i>

17
00:00:34,659 --> 00:00:35,535
What's your read?

18
00:00:35,618 --> 00:00:38,663
Does Dad know about
the projects I've been hiding?

19
00:00:39,205 --> 00:00:41,041
[in English] The real problem
is your sister.

20
00:00:41,583 --> 00:00:44,294
[Martina] <i>We need to find a way</i>
<i>for her to go back to the US.</i>

21
00:00:44,377 --> 00:00:46,337
[Mercado] <i>I told you</i>
<i>I won't be embarrassed.</i>

22
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:47,422
[Atoy] <i>What do you want?</i>

23
00:00:47,505 --> 00:00:49,048
I'll return this car to you.
Should I do it now?

24
00:00:49,132 --> 00:00:52,302
Actually, I'm outside with the client.

25
00:00:52,385 --> 00:00:53,845
[Mercado] <i>Ah, maybe just drop it here?</i>

26
00:00:53,928 --> 00:00:55,930
[Dmitri, in English] I'm Dmitri.
And you are?

27
00:00:56,556 --> 00:00:59,059
[in English] I'll just call you
the Master Cutter.

28
00:00:59,142 --> 00:01:00,602
[Audrey, in English] <i>I want to meet him.</i>

29
00:01:00,685 --> 00:01:02,437
<i>I think he can help me.</i>

30
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:03,813
[in English] My daughter is here.

31
00:01:04,856 --> 00:01:06,775
And it looks like she also wants
to ask you to find someone.

32
00:01:07,442 --> 00:01:08,818
[Atoy] <i>She's asking you</i>
<i>to find her ex-boyfriend, right?</i>

33
00:01:09,694 --> 00:01:12,155
Or maybe the guy who cheated on her.

34
00:01:12,238 --> 00:01:13,156
[in English] Dad!

35
00:01:14,199 --> 00:01:16,618
[music concludes]

36
00:01:16,701 --> 00:01:18,078
- [attendant] Uh, ma'am.
- Ah, yes?

37
00:01:18,161 --> 00:01:20,121
Ma'am, sorry. You parked
in a reserved slot.

38
00:01:20,205 --> 00:01:21,831
- Oh, sorry. I-- I didn't know.
- [mutters]

39
00:01:21,915 --> 00:01:23,416
- Okay, okay. I'll move it.
- [attendant] Okay.

40
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:24,584
[tense music playing]

41
00:01:24,667 --> 00:01:26,753
[Dmitri, in English] It seems
we have a chance to escape.

42
00:01:28,713 --> 00:01:29,756
[in English] What do you mean?

43
00:01:29,839 --> 00:01:31,341
[in English] My daughter is leaving.

44
00:01:32,383 --> 00:01:35,386
[in English] And thank you
for the swift return of my Draco.

45
00:01:35,470 --> 00:01:36,679
[in English] But I think
you'd better leave now.

46
00:01:36,763 --> 00:01:38,223
My daughter might come back.

47
00:01:39,015 --> 00:01:40,433
- [in English] Of course.
- [in English] Thank you, sir.

48
00:01:40,517 --> 00:01:43,561
Ah, just call me if you need me again.

49
00:01:44,145 --> 00:01:44,979
[in English] I will.

50
00:01:45,730 --> 00:01:46,564
[in English] Thank you, Colonel.

51
00:01:46,648 --> 00:01:48,191
Thank you very much.

52
00:01:48,274 --> 00:01:49,109
[in English] Sir.

53
00:01:49,192 --> 00:01:54,322
[sinister music playing]

54
00:01:57,951 --> 00:02:01,579
I think his daughter's ex is broke,

55
00:02:01,663 --> 00:02:03,665
that's why he doesn't
want them to get back together.

56
00:02:03,748 --> 00:02:04,582
[chuckles softly]

57
00:02:04,666 --> 00:02:07,252
That's why I avoid rich women, sir.

58
00:02:07,335 --> 00:02:09,796
Their families might
look down on us, right?

59
00:02:09,879 --> 00:02:11,381
We'd be doomed.

60
00:02:11,464 --> 00:02:12,590
Really, huh?

61
00:02:12,674 --> 00:02:14,175
[chuckles]

62
00:02:14,259 --> 00:02:15,343
[music concludes]

63
00:02:15,426 --> 00:02:17,971
I don't want to be punished, Sis Ame.

64
00:02:19,347 --> 00:02:22,892
Just apologize. Atoy has a point.

65
00:02:23,768 --> 00:02:27,230
But it seems he doesn't accept apologies.

66
00:02:27,313 --> 00:02:31,276
He's an old bachelor.
That's why he's grumpy!

67
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:33,319
[Tonet clears throat]

68
00:02:33,820 --> 00:02:35,405
Just relax, baby girl.

69
00:02:35,947 --> 00:02:39,367
I've got a solution,
so we won't get punished big time.

70
00:02:39,450 --> 00:02:42,078
- [Tonet chortles]
- Hmm? What will you do?

71
00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:44,789
- Act cute? Seduce him?
- Hmm?

72
00:02:44,873 --> 00:02:46,916
- Excuse me. I'm not like that.
- [whimsical music]

73
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,252
I'm conservative. Maybe that's your style.

74
00:02:49,335 --> 00:02:51,588
[Ame] Huh? Why would I do that?

75
00:02:51,671 --> 00:02:53,172
I was born cute.

76
00:02:54,382 --> 00:02:56,175
Anyway, I know what to do.

77
00:02:56,259 --> 00:02:58,970
I'll buy delicious barbecue

78
00:02:59,053 --> 00:03:01,306
to lighten Atoy's mood when he comes back.

79
00:03:02,390 --> 00:03:03,558
I've got you, baby girl.

80
00:03:03,641 --> 00:03:05,018
I'll handle it. [smooches]

81
00:03:05,685 --> 00:03:08,438
- Thank you, Sis Tonet!
- [Tonet] I'll be right back.

82
00:03:08,521 --> 00:03:10,064
[whimsical music playing]

83
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:12,859
Ibyang, it seems…

84
00:03:12,942 --> 00:03:14,527
you're siding with Tonet now.

85
00:03:14,611 --> 00:03:17,363
Like you prefer her for Atoy.

86
00:03:17,447 --> 00:03:21,200
Huh? You know,
I don't get you and Sis Tonet.

87
00:03:22,368 --> 00:03:25,580
It's obvious you both
have a crush on Master Grumpy!

88
00:03:27,081 --> 00:03:29,751
Why deny it to each other?

89
00:03:31,002 --> 00:03:33,212
[mutters] Whatever!

90
00:03:33,296 --> 00:03:38,343
Tonet mustn't notice, because she might…

91
00:03:38,426 --> 00:03:40,678
step up her moves on Atoy.

92
00:03:40,762 --> 00:03:42,055
I won't be able to catch up.

93
00:03:42,138 --> 00:03:43,556
My legs are short.

94
00:03:44,307 --> 00:03:47,894
What do you even like about Master Grumpy?

95
00:03:47,977 --> 00:03:50,772
Maybe he's never had a girlfriend,

96
00:03:50,855 --> 00:03:53,608
because he's… strict,

97
00:03:54,442 --> 00:03:58,321
snobbish, negative!

98
00:03:58,404 --> 00:03:59,614
[music concludes]

99
00:03:59,697 --> 00:04:03,243
Well, that's even better, that he's NGSB.

100
00:04:03,326 --> 00:04:06,579
So, I'll be his first girlfriend.

101
00:04:06,663 --> 00:04:09,040
- [chuckles softly]
- [quirky music playing]

102
00:04:09,123 --> 00:04:10,792
Oh my gosh!

103
00:04:11,542 --> 00:04:13,336
She's delusional now.

104
00:04:13,419 --> 00:04:17,465
[quirky music playing]

105
00:04:18,841 --> 00:04:20,218
[music concludes]

106
00:04:22,345 --> 00:04:26,891
[sinister music playing]

107
00:04:34,065 --> 00:04:35,108
[car blips]

108
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:57,088
[music intensifies]

109
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:02,552
[music concludes]

110
00:05:04,929 --> 00:05:06,514
Son of a thread!

111
00:05:07,432 --> 00:05:10,893
[epic music playing]

112
00:05:10,977 --> 00:05:12,437
- [horn honks]
- Hey!

113
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:14,314
[horn honks]

114
00:05:31,539 --> 00:05:32,415
[music concludes]

115
00:05:32,498 --> 00:05:36,919
[suave music playing]

116
00:06:00,443 --> 00:06:02,403
[music concludes]

117
00:06:04,781 --> 00:06:05,698
[in English] Gotcha.

118
00:06:08,618 --> 00:06:10,620
Son of a thread!

119
00:06:18,294 --> 00:06:22,090
[sinister music playing]

120
00:06:24,634 --> 00:06:25,635
[horn honks]

121
00:06:29,847 --> 00:06:31,265
[in English] Rude!

122
00:06:33,101 --> 00:06:34,310
[music concludes]

123
00:06:34,393 --> 00:06:36,604
Dad, I saw you with two guys earlier.

124
00:06:37,396 --> 00:06:40,399
- [in English] Who are they?
- [in English] Some friends I met here.

125
00:06:42,235 --> 00:06:44,237
Too bad, I wish I came earlier.

126
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:47,115
Then I could have met
your contact, the tracker.

127
00:06:47,198 --> 00:06:48,616
Oh, yes! About that,

128
00:06:48,699 --> 00:06:50,910
I mentioned you were interested,

129
00:06:50,993 --> 00:06:54,122
but unfortunately,
their client list is full.

130
00:06:54,205 --> 00:06:55,957
They said they'll update us when possible.

131
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:57,708
[in English] But…

132
00:06:58,876 --> 00:07:01,879
[scoffs] What exactly
are you… looking for?

133
00:07:02,547 --> 00:07:03,923
Or who?

134
00:07:04,006 --> 00:07:06,008
[pensive music playing]

135
00:07:06,092 --> 00:07:09,011
[in English] A man, actually.

136
00:07:10,805 --> 00:07:13,391
[in English] To be honest, Dad,
I don't even know his real name.

137
00:07:14,225 --> 00:07:17,186
I met him when I was living on the island.

138
00:07:18,396 --> 00:07:21,107
We were supposed to meet
before I disappeared, and…

139
00:07:21,858 --> 00:07:23,693
ever since I recovered…

140
00:07:24,902 --> 00:07:27,822
I've been wondering where he is…

141
00:07:28,990 --> 00:07:30,408
what happened to him.

142
00:07:32,535 --> 00:07:34,996
[in English] Do you think
he wonders about you too?

143
00:07:36,122 --> 00:07:37,707
Why didn't he look for you?

144
00:07:39,041 --> 00:07:40,376
[in English] I mean, maybe because…

145
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:42,753
Sweetheart, Audrey…

146
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:47,008
[in English] Look, it's been…
It's been eight years.

147
00:07:47,633 --> 00:07:51,262
[in English] Don't you think
it's about time you let go of that guy,

148
00:07:51,345 --> 00:07:52,972
and move on?

149
00:07:54,515 --> 00:07:56,350
[in English] For Christ's sake.

150
00:07:56,434 --> 00:07:58,728
[in English] You are a Regalia.

151
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:04,025
I don't want people thinking
you're the one chasing after a man.

152
00:08:05,776 --> 00:08:07,862
[in English] You deserve more than that.

153
00:08:11,532 --> 00:08:14,118
[somber music playing]

154
00:08:14,702 --> 00:08:15,703
[in English] Okay?

155
00:08:29,008 --> 00:08:30,510
[Karla] That's it.

156
00:08:32,762 --> 00:08:35,223
- [Ame] Rice?
- [Cita] Let's eat.

157
00:08:36,098 --> 00:08:37,558
[utensil clatter]

158
00:08:38,226 --> 00:08:40,645
[woman] <i>I've spoken to the families</i>
<i>of the other missing girls,</i>

159
00:08:40,728 --> 00:08:43,231
<i>and we believe they didn't elope.</i>

160
00:08:43,856 --> 00:08:45,733
<i>So, I hope that through this account,</i>

161
00:08:45,816 --> 00:08:47,527
<i>through this video I'm making,</i>

162
00:08:48,236 --> 00:08:50,905
<i>the police will finally</i>
<i>take their case seriously.</i>

163
00:08:50,988 --> 00:08:52,114
- [Tonet] Ah, Atoy, there's barbecue!
- [Ame] Brother Atoy!

164
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:54,617
Look, there's an issue now on FlipTok.

165
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:56,035
There are missing girls.

166
00:08:56,118 --> 00:08:58,287
The police said they eloped.

167
00:08:58,371 --> 00:08:59,789
But the families said

168
00:08:59,872 --> 00:09:02,833
they met someone on a dating app,
then disappeared?

169
00:09:02,917 --> 00:09:04,752
They're asking for help.

170
00:09:04,835 --> 00:09:05,962
[sinister music playing]

171
00:09:06,045 --> 00:09:07,797
Oh, but the police already knew that.

172
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:09,507
They know what to do.

173
00:09:09,590 --> 00:09:10,841
Just trust them.

174
00:09:11,467 --> 00:09:13,219
I'm hungry. What's this? What's this?

175
00:09:13,302 --> 00:09:16,180
The barbecue is from me and Sis Tonet!

176
00:09:16,264 --> 00:09:17,723
There's no poison in this, right?

177
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:20,601
Those dating apps are dangerous.

178
00:09:20,685 --> 00:09:22,311
Don't get involved in that!

179
00:09:22,395 --> 00:09:24,480
Yuck, Mom. I haven't
even thought about that.

180
00:09:24,564 --> 00:09:25,940
[Cita] Hmm.

181
00:09:26,023 --> 00:09:27,316
You too, Tonet.

182
00:09:27,984 --> 00:09:29,735
Oh, Miss Cita, you're too much.

183
00:09:29,819 --> 00:09:34,407
Why would I swipe there
if my TTH is just around?

184
00:09:34,490 --> 00:09:35,408
[Cita] Hmm?

185
00:09:35,491 --> 00:09:36,742
TTH, yuck.

186
00:09:36,826 --> 00:09:37,910
What do you mean by "yuck"?

187
00:09:38,494 --> 00:09:39,787
I ate a strand of hair.

188
00:09:39,870 --> 00:09:42,290
[quirky music playing]

189
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:44,834
- Atoy, one more?
- [Atoy] Mmm.

190
00:09:44,917 --> 00:09:46,377
I haven't even finished this yet.

191
00:09:46,460 --> 00:09:47,753
[man] Atoy?

192
00:09:51,465 --> 00:09:53,301
[Tonet] I-I'll do it. Water?

193
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:54,927
- [Ame] Rice?
- Ah… Oh, oh…

194
00:09:56,220 --> 00:09:57,305
Hungry, huh?

195
00:09:58,180 --> 00:09:59,348
- [mumbles]
- [Tonet] Okay.

196
00:09:59,432 --> 00:10:01,559
[quirky music continues]

197
00:10:01,642 --> 00:10:03,144
[Tonet] I gave him barbecue.

198
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:05,896
It had a lot of pepper.

199
00:10:05,980 --> 00:10:06,814
‪[music concludes]

200
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:11,152
Father, this task you gave is simple.

201
00:10:11,235 --> 00:10:12,361
I'll make sure that

202
00:10:12,445 --> 00:10:14,530
before your Sunday Mass begins,
this is done.

203
00:10:14,614 --> 00:10:15,948
Huh? I'll handle it, and…

204
00:10:16,866 --> 00:10:19,368
This one's on the house.
As usual, I'll take care of it.

205
00:10:19,452 --> 00:10:21,537
Hey, Atoy, that's business.

206
00:10:22,246 --> 00:10:23,414
But thanks, huh.

207
00:10:23,497 --> 00:10:24,957
[chuckles]

208
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:27,209
Uh, can Queenie pick it up instead?

209
00:10:28,169 --> 00:10:29,420
Sure.

210
00:10:30,087 --> 00:10:32,632
Oh, Queenie, say hi to Karla.

211
00:10:32,715 --> 00:10:34,800
Weren't you best friends before?

212
00:10:34,884 --> 00:10:38,220
- Um, we're still friends.
- [Atoy, in English] Shoulders, eight.

213
00:10:38,304 --> 00:10:39,805
That's right, Father.

214
00:10:39,889 --> 00:10:41,140
We just have different interests.

215
00:10:41,223 --> 00:10:44,685
I hope Karla becomes like Queenie.

216
00:10:44,769 --> 00:10:48,272
Look at her, such a lady and so modest.

217
00:10:48,356 --> 00:10:50,191
You must have many suitors, right?

218
00:10:50,274 --> 00:10:52,735
Oh, uh, I'm not allowed
to have a boyfriend.

219
00:10:52,818 --> 00:10:56,739
Uncle Father said only after I graduate.

220
00:10:56,822 --> 00:10:57,698
[chuckles]

221
00:10:57,782 --> 00:10:59,408
- [Atoy, in English] Twenty-three.
- Correct.

222
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:05,122
Honestly, I thank God
because my niece is so obedient.

223
00:11:05,206 --> 00:11:07,958
She doesn't give me problems. [chuckles]

224
00:11:08,042 --> 00:11:10,544
- Oh, Karla, did you hear that?
- [Karla] Oh, no!

225
00:11:11,170 --> 00:11:13,506
- Why me again?
- [Atoy, in English] Eighteen, armhole.

226
00:11:14,882 --> 00:11:16,801
Loosen this a bit.

227
00:11:16,884 --> 00:11:18,844
- [Cita chuckles]
- [mutters]

228
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:21,305
I'm gaining weight.

229
00:11:21,389 --> 00:11:22,807
[music concludes]

230
00:11:22,890 --> 00:11:24,809
[crickets chirping]

231
00:11:33,776 --> 00:11:36,153
Dad, shouldn't we be celebrating?

232
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:39,156
We found Draco.

233
00:11:40,366 --> 00:11:41,575
[in English] I'm not in the mood.

234
00:11:42,118 --> 00:11:43,244
Why? What's the problem?

235
00:11:43,744 --> 00:11:45,162
[in English] It's Audrey.

236
00:11:45,246 --> 00:11:46,997
[sinister music playing]

237
00:11:47,081 --> 00:11:49,333
[in English] Audrey wants
to look for some guy.

238
00:11:50,126 --> 00:11:52,920
A guy she met on an island.

239
00:11:54,171 --> 00:11:56,382
[in English] Though she
doesn't know his name.

240
00:11:57,675 --> 00:11:59,635
How do you find someone
without knowing his name?

241
00:12:00,261 --> 00:12:02,555
[in English] But she hasn't forgotten
about this guy.

242
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:05,599
What if…

243
00:12:06,517 --> 00:12:08,936
that man is important to Audrey?

244
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:10,646
What if…

245
00:12:11,814 --> 00:12:14,150
we made a mistake with what we did before?

246
00:12:14,233 --> 00:12:15,943
[in English] Dad, what's done is done.

247
00:12:16,986 --> 00:12:19,071
There's no point in thinking
about what we did.

248
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:22,616
[in English] What's important…
is that we protect our secret.

249
00:12:23,784 --> 00:12:25,161
[Audrey, in English] What secret?

250
00:12:25,244 --> 00:12:27,830
[music intensifies]

251
00:12:28,414 --> 00:12:32,209
[tense music playing]

252
00:12:33,836 --> 00:12:34,837
Um…

253
00:12:36,297 --> 00:12:38,591
Dad and I were talking
about his Kelso chicken.

254
00:12:38,674 --> 00:12:40,009
[sinister music playing]

255
00:12:40,092 --> 00:12:42,887
He wanted to file a case
against the one who took it…

256
00:12:43,637 --> 00:12:47,266
but it's better to keep
how it was taken a secret.

257
00:12:48,726 --> 00:12:51,937
[in English] Oh, did you want
something, Audrey?

258
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:54,064
[in English] Ah, yes.

259
00:12:54,148 --> 00:12:57,401
[in English] Um, I was thinking
about going away for a few days.

260
00:12:58,110 --> 00:13:01,197
[in English] Quick vacation,
just to clear my head.

261
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:02,990
[in English] I just wanted
to let you know, Dad.

262
00:13:03,574 --> 00:13:04,742
Where are you going?

263
00:13:06,285 --> 00:13:07,870
[in English] Do I need
to tell you everything?

264
00:13:09,246 --> 00:13:10,372
[in English] Fine.

265
00:13:11,123 --> 00:13:14,210
But bring someone from the staff,
so you'll have company.

266
00:13:14,293 --> 00:13:15,836
[in English] No, please. Dad, I just…

267
00:13:16,712 --> 00:13:18,130
wanna be alone for a while.

268
00:13:19,548 --> 00:13:20,591
[in English] Okay.

269
00:13:22,968 --> 00:13:24,178
[in English] Thanks.

270
00:13:24,261 --> 00:13:29,308
[tense music playing]

271
00:13:33,395 --> 00:13:34,563
[music concludes]

272
00:13:34,647 --> 00:13:35,814
Finish it.

273
00:13:36,565 --> 00:13:38,526
- [Tonet] Hmm.
- [Ame and Ibyang chuckle]

274
00:13:40,194 --> 00:13:42,071
- [Tonet] Hey, Atoy.
- Oh.

275
00:13:44,949 --> 00:13:46,492
Here's your share.

276
00:13:47,201 --> 00:13:50,204
- For helping me get the chicken.
- Ah.

277
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:52,331
[Tonet] No need, Atoy.

278
00:13:53,290 --> 00:13:56,544
- I'm just happy I helped you.
- Me too.

279
00:13:56,627 --> 00:13:59,463
Remember, if you need
my help again, just tell me.

280
00:14:00,589 --> 00:14:01,966
Me too, Atoy.

281
00:14:03,092 --> 00:14:04,969
I'll always be here for you. [titters]

282
00:14:05,844 --> 00:14:06,845
[Atoy] Refusing is not allowed.

283
00:14:07,429 --> 00:14:09,348
You worked for that,

284
00:14:09,431 --> 00:14:11,350
so you need to take your share.

285
00:14:11,850 --> 00:14:13,269
If not, people might say

286
00:14:13,352 --> 00:14:15,145
I'm taking advantage of your kindness.

287
00:14:15,229 --> 00:14:16,647
No, take it. It's yours.

288
00:14:17,439 --> 00:14:18,399
I'm fine with it.

289
00:14:18,482 --> 00:14:19,525
[quirky music playing]

290
00:14:20,109 --> 00:14:21,944
- Huh?
- Huh?

291
00:14:22,027 --> 00:14:26,115
No. What I said was,
you're really so kind, Atoy, yes.

292
00:14:26,198 --> 00:14:27,700
[in English] You're such
a good guy! [chuckles]

293
00:14:28,284 --> 00:14:30,870
That's why I'm Team Atoy. Go, team!

294
00:14:30,953 --> 00:14:32,663
[in English] Ah, Team Atoy?

295
00:14:32,746 --> 00:14:34,540
All this Team-Team Atoy talk…

296
00:14:34,623 --> 00:14:36,792
Can you stop with those team things?

297
00:14:36,876 --> 00:14:41,005
Honestly, I'm even thinking if I should
include you in the next operations.

298
00:14:41,088 --> 00:14:43,841
You're putting my plans at risk,

299
00:14:43,924 --> 00:14:45,175
because you're too stubborn.

300
00:14:45,926 --> 00:14:46,886
Huh?

301
00:14:46,969 --> 00:14:48,470
I'm really sorry!

302
00:14:48,554 --> 00:14:49,972
[mocking] "I'm really sorry."

303
00:14:50,514 --> 00:14:53,100
It's my fault too, Atoy.

304
00:14:53,183 --> 00:14:56,020
I just felt sorry for our baby girl.

305
00:14:56,103 --> 00:14:58,522
Oh, it wouldn't have
come to that if she hadn't left.

306
00:14:59,148 --> 00:15:01,025
Don't you realize what you did?

307
00:15:01,108 --> 00:15:02,610
It would've been fine if I
were the one who got into trouble.

308
00:15:02,693 --> 00:15:04,987
No problem, I can handle it.

309
00:15:05,070 --> 00:15:06,113
But what if it was Ame?

310
00:15:06,196 --> 00:15:08,282
What if something happened to her?

311
00:15:08,365 --> 00:15:09,491
[pensive music playing]

312
00:15:09,575 --> 00:15:11,911
What if it was Tonet?
What if something happened to Tonet?

313
00:15:14,079 --> 00:15:16,415
What about you?
What if something happened to you, huh?

314
00:15:17,666 --> 00:15:19,293
- Me?
- Yes.

315
00:15:20,336 --> 00:15:24,465
That means you care about me.

316
00:15:25,132 --> 00:15:27,051
- [Ibyang] Hee…
- Concerned?

317
00:15:27,134 --> 00:15:29,470
Ah, "concerned"? No, listen to me.

318
00:15:29,553 --> 00:15:32,723
If I say stay here, stay here!

319
00:15:32,806 --> 00:15:34,391
- Hmm?
- [Ibyang] Got it.

320
00:15:34,475 --> 00:15:35,309
Got it.

321
00:15:35,392 --> 00:15:37,937
But you have to admit
that you're concerned about me.

322
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:39,188
"Concerned"? What are you talking about?

323
00:15:39,271 --> 00:15:41,565
This kid really…

324
00:15:41,649 --> 00:15:43,817
always talking nonsense.

325
00:15:43,901 --> 00:15:45,235
[stammers] You-You, eat…

326
00:15:45,319 --> 00:15:46,946
Here. Just read instead.

327
00:15:47,696 --> 00:15:48,697
[Tonet] Mmm, there.

328
00:15:49,657 --> 00:15:51,742
Oh, just read instead.

329
00:15:54,078 --> 00:15:55,245
That's for you too.

330
00:16:00,876 --> 00:16:05,839
[gentle music playing]

331
00:16:19,311 --> 00:16:23,816
[boat engine whirring]

332
00:16:57,307 --> 00:17:01,270
[gentle music playing]

333
00:17:08,485 --> 00:17:09,695
[Vilma] Elaine!

334
00:17:10,612 --> 00:17:11,530
Vilma!

335
00:17:11,613 --> 00:17:13,490
Oh my God! It's really you!

336
00:17:13,574 --> 00:17:14,366
[shrieks]

337
00:17:14,450 --> 00:17:16,243
- Vilma! [giggles]
- [Vilma] How are you?

338
00:17:16,326 --> 00:17:17,494
[Vilma] Wait. Oh my god.

339
00:17:18,162 --> 00:17:19,371
You look so different now!

340
00:17:19,455 --> 00:17:20,497
You've become even more beautiful!

341
00:17:20,581 --> 00:17:22,207
- You are too.
- Oh, wait!

342
00:17:22,291 --> 00:17:24,126
What happened to you?

343
00:17:24,209 --> 00:17:25,794
We were worried about you.

344
00:17:25,878 --> 00:17:28,297
You suddenly left without saying goodbye.

345
00:17:29,089 --> 00:17:31,258
It's… It's a long story.

346
00:17:31,341 --> 00:17:34,636
Uh… There was a family emergency and…

347
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:36,722
[in English] I had to leave
the country with my dad and…

348
00:17:37,347 --> 00:17:38,390
work on some things.

349
00:17:38,474 --> 00:17:40,976
But you didn't even contact us.

350
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:43,103
You disappeared for years.

351
00:17:43,771 --> 00:17:45,898
I even searched for you on social media.

352
00:17:45,981 --> 00:17:49,693
But you didn't have
a profile page. [sighs]

353
00:17:49,777 --> 00:17:53,155
You know, I even thought you were gone.

354
00:17:53,822 --> 00:17:55,824
I'm so sorry, Vilma.

355
00:17:55,908 --> 00:17:58,869
- [Vilma] Hmm.
- So many things happened back then.

356
00:17:59,828 --> 00:18:01,705
But I'm here now,

357
00:18:02,414 --> 00:18:03,832
and I'm still alive!

358
00:18:04,416 --> 00:18:05,751
[in English] Thank God!

359
00:18:05,834 --> 00:18:08,420
Why did you just visit now?

360
00:18:09,171 --> 00:18:12,966
I just got back from the States
since I left here.

361
00:18:13,050 --> 00:18:13,967
[Vilma sighs]

362
00:18:14,051 --> 00:18:15,886
[Audrey] I missed you all
here on the island.

363
00:18:15,969 --> 00:18:17,262
We missed you too.

364
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:21,308
I'm looking for someone.

365
00:18:21,391 --> 00:18:22,351
[Vilma] Ah. [sighs]

366
00:18:23,352 --> 00:18:25,813
Okay. Wait, wait, wait! Wait.

367
00:18:25,896 --> 00:18:26,980
Belen!

368
00:18:27,064 --> 00:18:28,565
Elaine is here!

369
00:18:29,441 --> 00:18:31,860
[nostalgic music playing]

370
00:18:31,944 --> 00:18:32,986
[sighs]

371
00:18:33,612 --> 00:18:36,323
The last time I saw him was at your hut…

372
00:18:37,074 --> 00:18:38,784
and he was looking for you.

373
00:18:39,326 --> 00:18:42,788
He was also surprised when you left
without saying goodbye.

374
00:18:44,164 --> 00:18:45,290
[sighs]

375
00:18:45,374 --> 00:18:47,000
He came back for me?

376
00:18:48,335 --> 00:18:51,088
[gentle music playing]

377
00:18:51,171 --> 00:18:54,341
Vilma, where could I find him?

378
00:18:55,342 --> 00:18:58,137
Elaine, why do you want to see him?

379
00:18:58,720 --> 00:19:00,681
Were you in a relationship before?

380
00:19:00,764 --> 00:19:01,849
[scoffs]

381
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:04,059
[Vilma scoffs]

382
00:19:04,143 --> 00:19:05,727
When you left,

383
00:19:05,811 --> 00:19:08,147
didn't you hear about what happened here?

384
00:19:09,106 --> 00:19:11,859
The man you're looking for was involved.

385
00:19:13,527 --> 00:19:14,736
What-what happened?

386
00:19:15,988 --> 00:19:17,948
There was chaos here before.

387
00:19:18,532 --> 00:19:22,703
He killed the bodyguards
of the Italian visitor.

388
00:19:22,786 --> 00:19:25,414
There was even an explosion at sea.

389
00:19:25,956 --> 00:19:27,291
The news we heard

390
00:19:27,875 --> 00:19:30,127
was that they were military spies.

391
00:19:31,044 --> 00:19:32,045
[Vilma sighs]

392
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:34,339
It was intense.

393
00:19:35,048 --> 00:19:36,508
Part of his plan

394
00:19:36,592 --> 00:19:38,927
was to get to know
and win the trust of the people here

395
00:19:39,011 --> 00:19:40,596
for their operation.

396
00:19:42,222 --> 00:19:43,223
[Audrey shrieks]

397
00:19:43,307 --> 00:19:45,517
[gentle music playing]

398
00:19:47,352 --> 00:19:48,187
‪[sighs]

399
00:19:48,270 --> 00:19:51,523
So, your suspicion was right
that he didn't have amnesia,

400
00:19:51,607 --> 00:19:54,151
because he was just pretending.

401
00:19:54,776 --> 00:19:57,613
Wow, he was a liar.

402
00:19:57,696 --> 00:19:59,907
He used the kindness of the people here.

403
00:19:59,990 --> 00:20:01,033
[music concludes]

404
00:20:01,116 --> 00:20:03,619
- But he didn't…
- [Vilma scoffs]

405
00:20:03,702 --> 00:20:06,079
do anything bad to the locals, right?

406
00:20:06,163 --> 00:20:09,583
No, because he had another agenda.

407
00:20:09,666 --> 00:20:11,710
That's why he kept approaching you, right?

408
00:20:11,793 --> 00:20:14,046
You were the only one who doubted him,

409
00:20:14,129 --> 00:20:17,716
so he won your trust right away
so he wouldn't be exposed.

410
00:20:17,799 --> 00:20:19,927
[gentle music playing]

411
00:20:20,427 --> 00:20:22,262
Looks like that's what happened.

412
00:20:25,015 --> 00:20:26,433
[Vilma] Did you fall for him?

413
00:20:26,934 --> 00:20:28,268
Were you in a relationship?

414
00:20:28,352 --> 00:20:30,896
[scoffs, in English] No. No way!

415
00:20:30,979 --> 00:20:33,023
How could I fall for him?

416
00:20:33,106 --> 00:20:34,858
[in English] I don't even know
his real name.

417
00:20:35,442 --> 00:20:36,610
That's true!

418
00:20:36,693 --> 00:20:39,279
Who would be foolish enough to fall
for a man you don't even know, right?

419
00:20:39,863 --> 00:20:40,822
[in English] Right? [scoffs]

420
00:20:41,990 --> 00:20:44,076
But if you were there
when he came back to your house,

421
00:20:44,743 --> 00:20:47,246
you probably would've
been together then, right?

422
00:20:47,329 --> 00:20:48,121
[scoffs]

423
00:20:48,205 --> 00:20:50,582
There was something between you before.

424
00:20:51,541 --> 00:20:56,505
- [sentimental music playing]
- [both scoff]

425
00:20:59,132 --> 00:21:04,930
[nostalgic music playing]

426
00:21:26,535 --> 00:21:27,995
It's nice living on the island.

427
00:21:29,621 --> 00:21:31,456
The air is clean.

428
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:33,792
Life is simple…

429
00:21:34,918 --> 00:21:36,295
The people are happy.

430
00:21:36,878 --> 00:21:38,714
Have you seen the sunset here?

431
00:21:38,797 --> 00:21:40,716
Mmm. It's beautiful.

432
00:21:40,799 --> 00:21:42,843
But it's even more beautiful if…

433
00:21:44,678 --> 00:21:49,641
you have someone holding
your hand while watching it, right?

434
00:21:49,725 --> 00:21:51,059
[chuckles]

435
00:21:51,643 --> 00:21:53,103
[in English] What a sweet talker.

436
00:22:00,068 --> 00:22:03,864
[gentle music playing]

437
00:22:03,947 --> 00:22:05,115
We're even.

438
00:22:13,874 --> 00:22:15,709
Maybe that's really where it ends.

439
00:22:19,504 --> 00:22:20,672
[in English] Nothing more.

440
00:22:30,599 --> 00:22:31,516
Hey.

441
00:22:32,309 --> 00:22:33,226
You've been there for a while.

442
00:22:33,310 --> 00:22:35,020
Where's the book I asked you to read?

443
00:22:35,937 --> 00:22:36,938
Huh?

444
00:22:37,522 --> 00:22:39,483
Instead of playing games all the time.

445
00:22:40,067 --> 00:22:41,151
Read it! Go!

446
00:22:41,818 --> 00:22:45,363
That book is boring. It made me sleepy.

447
00:22:45,864 --> 00:22:47,324
[in English] Boring?

448
00:22:47,407 --> 00:22:48,283
That's a really good book.

449
00:22:48,366 --> 00:22:49,951
It was my favorite when I was a kid.

450
00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:51,787
Come on, read it now.

451
00:22:51,870 --> 00:22:54,915
Don't be lazy. You're so lazy.
You're playing games all the time.

452
00:22:54,998 --> 00:22:56,041
Go on!

453
00:22:56,124 --> 00:22:57,417
[gentle music playing]

454
00:22:57,501 --> 00:22:58,335
Oh.

455
00:23:00,629 --> 00:23:02,547
[Atoy] Hmm? Oh, what happened?

456
00:23:03,423 --> 00:23:05,383
Nothing. I'm just fixing it.

457
00:23:06,134 --> 00:23:07,844
"Once upon a time…"

458
00:23:08,637 --> 00:23:11,181
"Once upon a time"? What's that?

459
00:23:11,264 --> 00:23:13,016
Is that a history story?

460
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:14,726
No, just read it.

461
00:23:14,810 --> 00:23:16,603
[music concludes]

462
00:23:16,686 --> 00:23:19,106
"There was a beautiful princess

463
00:23:20,232 --> 00:23:27,030
on a faraway island,
and she was with the swimming fishes."

464
00:23:27,114 --> 00:23:30,117
[quirky music playing]

465
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:31,660
Then?

466
00:23:32,327 --> 00:23:33,829
- [Atoy] Fish?
- "Then someone jo--"

467
00:23:35,872 --> 00:23:36,790
[chuckles]

468
00:23:36,873 --> 00:23:39,751
That's not what's written here.
There are no fish.

469
00:23:39,835 --> 00:23:41,044
You're making things up.

470
00:23:41,670 --> 00:23:43,713
Well, this book is boring,

471
00:23:43,797 --> 00:23:45,924
so I made the story better.

472
00:23:46,007 --> 00:23:46,925
- [Atoy] Ah!
- [Uh…

473
00:23:47,008 --> 00:23:48,802
- See, isn't that better?
- [scoffs]

474
00:23:48,885 --> 00:23:50,887
So, Ibyang is a writer
after all, Brother Atoy!

475
00:23:50,971 --> 00:23:52,264
[Atoy] Oh, wow!

476
00:23:52,347 --> 00:23:54,641
You're actually good at making up stories.

477
00:23:54,724 --> 00:23:55,976
So, what happened to the fish?

478
00:23:56,059 --> 00:23:58,436
Then, after that, what happened?

479
00:23:58,520 --> 00:23:59,604
Atoy!

480
00:23:59,688 --> 00:24:01,189
Father, perfect timing!

481
00:24:01,273 --> 00:24:03,024
I was about to deliver your cassock.

482
00:24:03,108 --> 00:24:05,318
Queenie didn't pick it up.

483
00:24:05,402 --> 00:24:07,237
Well, that's the problem.

484
00:24:07,904 --> 00:24:09,364
Why, Father? What's the problem?

485
00:24:09,447 --> 00:24:10,448
[tense music playing]

486
00:24:10,532 --> 00:24:12,200
Atoy, Queenie is missing.

487
00:24:12,284 --> 00:24:14,035
They need your help.

488
00:24:14,119 --> 00:24:15,287
[Karla] Huh?

489
00:24:20,083 --> 00:24:22,169
[electronic blipping]

490
00:24:22,252 --> 00:24:25,172
[music intensifies]

491
00:24:30,468 --> 00:24:32,137
Help us find my niece.

492
00:24:32,220 --> 00:24:33,847
Well, where could she have gone?

493
00:24:33,930 --> 00:24:35,307
Where can we find this Jeff?

494
00:24:35,390 --> 00:24:37,851
[Karla] <i>He might be behind</i>
<i>Queenie's disappearance.</i>

495
00:24:37,934 --> 00:24:41,438
[grunting and groaning]

496
00:24:41,521 --> 00:24:42,731
- [bone snaps]
- [man shrieks]

497
00:24:42,814 --> 00:24:45,483
You know, Atoy's new assistant
is really a chick, right?

498
00:24:45,567 --> 00:24:47,027
Just snobbish.

499
00:24:47,110 --> 00:24:49,404
[Ame] <i>Are you hiding from Emerson?</i>

500
00:24:50,155 --> 00:24:51,907
Why would I hide from him?
Who is he anyway?

501
00:24:51,990 --> 00:24:55,619
- Well, your crush!
- What?!

502
00:24:55,702 --> 00:24:56,953
If I hadn't listened to you,

503
00:24:57,579 --> 00:24:59,331
we wouldn't be hiding
anything from Audrey!

504
00:24:59,414 --> 00:25:02,083
And I'm dreading the day the wound opens,

505
00:25:02,167 --> 00:25:03,501
and everything is revealed!

506
00:25:03,585 --> 00:25:04,920
But that won't happen, right?

507
00:25:05,003 --> 00:25:07,839
Because only the three of us know,
and no one will tell her.

508
00:25:07,923 --> 00:25:10,467
Ah, Father, let's just meet at…
Queenie's house.

509
00:25:10,550 --> 00:25:11,635
Get some matches!

510
00:25:11,718 --> 00:25:12,761
UP NEXT

